cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about using convolutional neural networks for segmenting stroke lesions in brain MRI images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training and testing neural networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques and the development of a new system for stroke lesion segmentation could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of 3D convolutional neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
